HEADWORD: Jararaca
<hw>Jar`a*ra"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg., from the
native name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A poisonous serpent of
Brazil (<spn>Bothrops jararaca</spn>), about eighteen inches long, and
of a dusky, brownish color, variegated with red and black
spots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

